messages.message:
we have a lot of recent bug reports ->let's try to prioritize so that the BE engineers (@ayesha.ali @prateek.tenkale @Sayan) can pull together to debug the highest priority bugs together

:question-block:  root cause unknown
:eyes:  root cause known

1. :question-block: Fannie Mae - doc disappearing bc of discrepancy between FS vs DB (https://instabase.slack.com/archives/CKBRX13L5/p1746567239899629?thread_ts=1746487852.849759&cid=CKBRX13L5)
    a. after this error, gt set is not able to be used for accuracy test
    b. workaround: create new gt set
    c. seems to be similar to https://instabase.atlassian.net/browse/EPD-3128, which we never fixed for Velocity :smiling_face_with_tear:  
2. :question-block: Fannie Mae - unique constraint error when remapping records (https://instabase.slack.com/archives/C011FHLBN8N/p1746632970816559)
    a. intermittent, doesn't prevent gt set from being used for accuracy test
    b. we don't know yet if this is causing the blocker issue above ^
3. :question-block: Fannie Mae - re-extraction "no value found" issue (https://instabase.slack.com/archives/C05BJCNKZAM/p1746635064536649)
    a. intermittent
    b. workaround: manually typing in field values
4. :question-block: Nationwide - review dashboard missing docs (https://instabase.slack.com/archives/C05BJCNKZAM/p1746563980486969)
    a. workaround ?
5. :eyes: Commercial - email upstream integration permission issue (https://instabase.slack.com/archives/C05BJCNKZAM/p1745886274918409)
    a. workaround ?
6. :eyes: Fannie Mae - docs with classification validation failures not showing up in review dashboard (https://instabase.atlassian.net/browse/EPD-4284)
    a. workaround: review by clicking deployment run link and removing deploymentId from URL :grimacing: 
7. :question-block: Soleng - field edits not getting saved in Human Review (https://instabase.slack.com/archives/C05BJCNKZAM/p1746539580840139)
    a. workaround ?
@jack.robbins can you weigh in how to prioritize these?

additionally one prateek is working on:
• Fannie Mae - classification validation failures not showing up in doc reviews https://instabase.atlassian.net/browse/EPD-4284
the first fannie mae issue is being worked around for now by recreating gt sets
thanks just added that one to the list!
'classification validation failures not showing up in doc reviews' I believe I've identified the issue, just need to think through the fix
just had a call with suleiman and abhishek about 3, we were able to reproduce locally, abhishek will look into it https://instabase.atlassian.net/browse/EPD-4315

Ayesha Sayan Serena and I were talking about it, it seems like #1 and #2 are related so it makes the most sense for one person to look at those two together. #3 is already being taken care of by Abhishek. #4 is not a bug but rather a potential product improvement that needs product / design input, so we will hold off on that. The plan is:
• I will take a look at #1 and #2 and investigate / reproduce on my end. Will continue work on #6 after #1 and #2 are addressed
• Abhishek is looking at #3
• #4 is not a bug
• Sayan will look at #5
• Ayesha will look into #7

confirming on #4 - we note in the Deployment docs (https://docs.instabase.com/apps/run-and-deploy#creating-deployments):

> Review by file — Sends only files that fail validation for human review, and assigns reviews by file.
